A councillor in Alexandra township is accused of only giving government food parcels to ANC supporters. Residents say the councillor is also chasing away NGOs that want to distribute food parcels in the area. #Day41ofLockdown Courtesy of #DStv403 ALEXANDRA - A councillor in Alexandra township is being accused of only giving government food parcels to ANC supporters. Residents said the councillor is also chasing away NGOs that want to distribute food parcels in the area. In KwaZulu-Natal, some ANC leaders have filmed themselves giving away food parcels and posting their videos on social media. READ: Chaos in Alexandra over food parcels It's alleged this is to score cheap political points. Other party leaders have been accused of stealing food parcels that's just some of the issues discussed at a PEC meeting. READ: Mitchells Plain pensioners claim food parcels tampered with ANC spokesperson Pule Mabe said the government will act swiftly and decisively in cases where there is evidence of wrongdoing. Mabe said social relief programmes must be coordinated with oversight mechanisms. Mabe said government officials must not attract reproach through their actions during the COVID-19 pandemic. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.